E EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><body><p><img border="0" src="http://omega.uta.edu/~dak4238/banner1.jpg"></p></body></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulivtinth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Livtinth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Maztah Pozter</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/01 3:31:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> i have played a bard as well and i still would not compare them to any caster. a bard is for me kind of a melee (weak hybrid) who can wear plate, and sing songs. the real strengths of a bard are his songs. so, a druid gets a lot of utility spells, that's right. but spells and songs are quite a different thing. bards can't bind, bards don't have gate (=melee hybrid). BUT they are able to use a form of magic (their songs) which makes their travel faster, lets them heal their group, haste the group, increase resistances, even mezz mobs or charm them, or &quot;snare&quot; them.<br><br>bards are much more than a &quot;melee druid&quot;. and there would certainly be more bards if the class wouldn't have its problems at lower levels while being one of the most difficult EQ classes overall too.<br><br>someinputfrombardsplzkkthx! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shift? What's Shift?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/31/01 4:37:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure Casidy would classify herself as a melee-Druid, but I'll ask her to take a look at this thread when she gets on-line. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR><I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/31/01 4:53:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> Bard and druid really have nothing in common. In fact Bard and any other class have nothing in common really. Then again a bard and Every class have something in common. Confusing eh? Well a bard has a little bit from Every class in the game. Actually only the necro comes close to being this versatile. <br><br>While a Druid may have utility spells they are quite linear in nature. Also druid do not have a spell for every occation either. &lt;Also has a 55 druid&gt; <br><br>Bards are unique to the world of Norrath. The ablility to juggle 3 songs maybe a 4th on a good day. The ability to run faster than anything on the planet, to heal, mana regen, Dot, even dd a little, kite, fear kit, mez, charm, occasionally stun, create dmg shields, str/agil/dex buff, mini rune, haste, invis, evade, lull pull, debuff, slow, snare, Group invul &lt;at lvl 60&gt; shadow step, melee a bit as well and are GODS of resist. There are few other things we can do but is restricted by time of day. Bards make others Stronger around them. Their songs stack with spells that normally dont allow other spells to stack with them. <br><br>Bards are still not well understood and those that have a twink lvl 20 bard still have no real clue to what they can do. Bards have very defining moments in their career where they go through a serious metamorphasis at several stages. While for pure power, most classes are more powerful, I cannot count how many times the bard has saved the day. I cannot count how many times I have been told, &quot;Wow, I did not know you could do that&quot; when saving the day. <br><br>I read threads where the question is.... What songs do you mainly use? I hate this question. It show a lack of understanding of the class. That question is so hard to answer because it depends on the situation. What mobs are you fighting? What is your group composition? What zone are you in? Is it day or night? What race are the members of your Group? There are several permutations for a bard. Once again a song for every occasion. Bards limit down time severly and can fill the role of about every class. Cleric being the one we really cannot compensate for. But In the past when I have been in groups with no cleric and have a shaman and another decent healer, I have been known to whip out the banjo and twist Niv's and Catana to keep the group at full health. Only the necro seems to have close to this much versatility. <br><br>Our strenght lies in our subtlety, most have no clue to what we are even doing for them. I have received many a tell where after I left the group saying, &quot;Man we were killing so much faster with you in the group.&quot; Now if we just had a group intra zone succor song that would rule. he he<br><br>Also the bard is the only class I know of that can help a group while AFK as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Hopefully this will give a better understanding of the bard. I know there are other very competent bards out there that could probably add to this and I have not mentioned everything we can do and definately not in detail. Of all the classes I have played the bard is still my favorite hands down bar none. Even when we had the XP penalties, I would not have given up my bard for the world. There are some minor tweaks I would like to see done for the bard but other than that they by far take the most skill and attention to detail of any other class in the game.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br><br><br><br><br> <p>Cuthbert Dirgewielder <BR>El Virtuoso and Uber Geek of F.U.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ushamanpimp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shamanpimp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/10/01 11:16:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> hrm.. this is a pretty vague question... seems basically what youre asking is what class is the best :P<br><br>druids can quad kite with ease, and can travel with ease<br><br>clerics arguably the best epic effect in game for raid purposes, and get the most overpowered spell in the game: complete heal.. and even a group version<br><br>shaman  are the most gear dependent casters, as they get some of the best item effects for soloing (epic and jb bracer petty much enable manaless kills) and raiding purposes (buffs from jb armor/ velious armor / and a couple other items, ie VP primal stick &amp; snare spear)...  and have quite a few things available to them first hand that they wouldnt be able to do on thier own with alchemy (gate potions, personal damage shields).  cannabalize 3/4 + torpor + regrow + bear form + racial regen (troll/iksar) + fungi shirt + fungi stick (only really useful outdoors) =  insane mana regen... hence many shaman dont see wis as too critical a stat as clerics/druids, and opt for more hp and ac gear... you take away these items, soloing shaman would probably drop by 2/3<br><br>i agree with Mr Geek that bards are pretty versitile, and imo, very inderrated as a class... most people don't probly dont expect much more than mana/hp regen, and unfortunately, thats all that some will do<br><br>as far as spell sets, you can't really compare... as each class is really designed for its own thing... <br><br>if youre going for diversity, its bard... <br><br>if youre going for spells that will rake in solo xp, i guess its druids due to quad kiting... <br><br>if youre going for group ability, id give clerics an edge over shaman only because of experience resurrections and complete healing: the sole cause of the insane mob hp in velious...  these 2 spells are what unbalances clerics to where they are required to do anything worthwhile (group/raid wise) in much of the world post 50... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/13/01 2:11:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> /agree Mogur, but I would add that a lot of people are making characters based on, which does most dmg. Sad state of affairs there. I say pick a class that suits your personality. I chose the bard cause I am a self absorbed, Vain, attention seeking, attention deficeit performer. Just could not be avoided. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As for what got the most. Hmmmm hard to say, and at what lvl of the game are you refering to. Hell from lvl 1 to 15 bard is the most powerful melee in the game other than monk. Then other classes start getting dual wield and double attack. Also then the mobs start getting much harder for what the con to you. There is a point in game where ranger is god melee, then warrior is the god melee and rogues can outdamage wizards. So, who got the most? Verant did. They are raking in about 3 million a month from us hehe. <p><BR> <BR><img src="http://omega.uta.edu/~dak4238/sigs/cuthbert.jpg" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udammur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dammur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/1/01 4:52:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://64.77.120.194/Dammur1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> If we are talking about which has gotten the most improvements since the release of eq...<br><br>rogues have had their abilities greatilly boosted, they are now arguably the most powerful in the game.<br><br>Warriors had their abilities boosted with kunark.  In addition they have been given spells on their armor, some of which are better then spells that hybreds get (ie. warriors get invis, a spell that paladin's would kill for)<br><br>Monks have become even more amazing since the advent of the fungi tunic.<br><br>Shammys....i have not fought with them much pre kunark, but post 50, post kunark, they are a force to be reconned with.<br><br><br>Conversilly,<br>Paladin's relative strength compared to warriors has worsened.<br><br>Rangers used to take damage as good as warriors (back in the rubicite days).  now there is a great margin in terms of hp, and a large margin in terms of ac as well.  their damage output still kicks ass though<br><br>Necromancers have been showned the true meaning of 'nerf.'  There used to be a time that a 50 necromancer could do what entire guilds had difficulity doing (ie, there used to be guild raids on frenzy room in guk.  a necro would turn around and solo it and laugh.  Now i hear many necros complain that they have no place on guild raids other then 'mana feeder'.  (personally i disagree.  after fighting with palimax in raids, i am convinced that a well played necromancer is still as good as any other class on a raid situation)<br><br><br>All of these (of course) depend on how well your play your character.  I would rather have a good ranger as primary tank on a raid, then i would have a poorily played warrior tanking.<br><br>Dammur<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udammur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dammur</A> at: 7/2/01 3:21:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukaitansk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaitan SK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/3/01 2:08:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.co