br>Bard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>p.s.  No way I'm going in depth as Cuthbert.  I discuss the class enough in tells. &lt;eg&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383836><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ueniumar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eniumar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/8/02 1:49:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1>  I may be biased because i am one but imo a chanter is the most biased class in the game. verant nerfs them continually because of the abilities they have and will continue to do so they have fixed bugs and changed mobs to tone us down granted verse high end mobs we are no more then buff whores but imagine doing them high end mobs without them.<br> I have seen groups from when i was 1 60 existing in every camp in the game with diferent classes but honestly never without a chanter for most of them wizards want our buff warriors and every one else.<br> If I had to post who is the absolute most evil class for soloing i would say bard they are so versatile and have the abilities of every class and with the proper twisting and skills no class matches them in this aspect. Of course with enchanters and the in flux of high end seb gear and kunark drops becoming twink gear they are not as essential as once were in groups. Still though we are still wanted in alot of groups for the safety we provide thru mez.<br>we will have to see exactly on what and who dire charm will work on and what it is able to effect to see what happens to enchanters in the future we may become more of a traditional solo class like the mage, necromancer, wizard druid and several others have become in our ever changing world do to equipment available and abilities developing.<br> As for clerics i see them as easily as powerful as any other class in the game thru the power of ch and large bonuses of hit points gifted thru the use of their heroic bond and symbol lines of spells. They are absoluntely essential for almost all high end mobs where almost any other class can be eliminated or done without. Just may take longer to kill the same mobs.<br> I realize i did not say this one or that one is the best overall but what is best depends on lvls abilities and gear. And also how well someone is able to play their class in my opinion every class is the most powerful in the right encounter that  they appear to be neeeded for. And i say  that they appear to be needed for because i have seen sks do a monks job, rangers do a chanters, chanters do a clerics, rogues do a warriors, necros do a mages, wizards do a chanters, druids do a warriors, and so on and so on<br> So i say to you this do not think one class is more powerful then another for it is not the class to make the abilities but yet the person behind that toon being able to improvise and think that makes them powerful.<br><br>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urolielkotn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RolielKotN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/8/02 3:48:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Class got most Bonus from VI ?</span><hr size=1> Bards are neat - I agree with Cuthbert, there is a lot we can do that people are unaware of.<br><br>Bet you didn't know bards can do over 2k damage in a minute with DoT's. <br><br>Did you know I can get a regen of about 45 hp a tick going with two songs?<br><br>I can nearly negate damage done to my group using a rune song, with a shaman or enchanter around to slow. Neat trick, huh?<br><br>I think the strong point of a bard is adaptability. There is very, very little I cannot do, though I don't do most of those things as well as other classes (this is where the druid thing comes in, I think - druids are also a &quot;jack of all trades, master of none&quot; class). It's important to learn what to do in different situations; for instance, I'm doing a lot of different stuff if I'm grouped with a shaman or enchanter. I also need to judge whether my group would be better off with an offensive or defensive boost. If I'm grouped with four warriors and a cleric, you can bet your ass I'm singing haste over cantata, should I have to pick.<br><br>I also agree that a lot of the things we do for a group are subtle. After 50, I started to shift towards making my group as efficient as possible. If you cannot swap instruments in when your songs take effect, and melee the rest of the time, consider not meleeing. Shield of Songs is extremely powerful with a lute out - worth more to your group than your melee damage in most cases.<br><br>Bards are cool, if you know what you're doing. I'll quote Kleg here: &quot;A good bard is worth his weight in plat. A bad one is just a pain in the ass.&quot; If you know the right thing to do given the situation, your group will love you. If not, chances are you're just going to frustrate people.<br><br> <p><IMG SRC=http://www.tiannathomas.com/images/roliel3.gif><small><br>-------------- Proud member of the Valiant Crusaders, Ayonae Ro ---------------</small></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showMessage?topicID=107.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbs